  "narrative": "3.125(a) \n   \nFacilities, general. \nThe enclosure housing a kinkajou has a wire mesh approximately .5 X .5 inches in size surrounding a wooden frame. On \nthe front panel of the enclosure, the mesh contains a hole measuring approximately 2.5 X 4 inches. The broken wire \nsurrounding the hole has created multiple sharp edges that protrude inward into the enclosure. \n \nSharp edges may pose a risk of injury to the animal through cuts, abrasions, or entanglement if the animal comes into \ncontact with the damaged mesh. \n \nHousing facilities shall be maintained in good repair to protect the animals from injury and to contain the animals. \nCorrected at the time of inspection, March 11, 2026. \n \nThis inspection and exit interview were conducted with a facility representative. \n \n n",
